President Barack Obama has proclaimed March 2, 2012, as Read Across America Day. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of reading in enriching the human experience and fostering learning, opportunity, and success. Obama calls upon parents, caregivers, teachers, librarians, and public officials to celebrate this day by promoting reading through various programs and activities. He also highlights the birthday of author Theodor Seuss Geisel (Dr. Seuss), whose imaginative stories continue to inspire young readers worldwide. Obama reaffirms his commitment to providing every child with an outstanding education and encourages all Americans to participate in observing Read Across America Day.